iger's milk, is the Peruvian term for a citrus-based marinade that cures the seafood in a ceviche. Also known as leche de pantera, this leftover fish runoff usually contains lime juice, sliced onion, chillies, salt and pepper - along with some fish juice. <br>In Peru, this invigorating potion is often served alongside ceviche in a small glass and believed to be both a hangover cure as well as an aphrodisiac!"],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}